<HR><H2>Driver list of bugs/problems</H2>
<H3>daemon@ATHENA.MIT.EDU (Sun Nov 19 17:21:08 1995
)</H3>
<PRE>
Date: Sun, 19 Nov 1995 15:03:44 -0700
From: 869683 Gillespie Brandon James &lt;brandon@petersboro.declab.usu.edu&gt;
To: coldstuff@tombstone.sunrem.com

Ok, the current list of problems has been dramatically reduced over the past
few months.  I'm posting it now with christmas break approaching where more
people will have some extra time available.  If anybody finds any clues leading
to the whereabouts of a solution for these problems, let us know.

    * textdumping randomly leaves out objects after the db reaches
      a certain size, coldcore has an in-db dumping mechanism to
      get around this, as textdumping is being rewritten.
    * callers() causes a SEGV sometimes (but not always).  It is
      used in .debug() in coldcore, so you may want to remove this.
    * tasks() causes a SEGV most times.

-Brandon Gillespie-
</PRE>
